advice.title: Elevated Concern
advice.message: Chest pain can be serious. Seek urgent medical attention or call emergency services if severe, sudden, radiating, or with shortness of breath.

advice.title: Fever Detected
advice.message: Monitor temperature, hydrate, and rest. If fever exceeds 103°F (39.4°C), lasts >3 days, or pairs with chest pain or shortness of breath, seek care promptly.

advice.title: Dizziness Noted
advice.message: Sit or lie down to avoid falls, hydrate, and rise slowly. If severe, persistent, fainting, or with chest pain/shortness of breath, seek care.

advice.title: Sore Throat Noted
advice.message: Hydrate, use warm saline gargles, and rest. If severe pain, trouble swallowing, or high fever, seek medical advice.
